-- Go-Ahead, Micro Focus, Petrofac, Barclays: U.K., Irish Equity Preview
-- Ben Martin
-- 2010-06-24T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/go-ahead-micro-focus-petrofac-barclays-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  
 The benchmark  FTSE 100 Index  fell 68.46, or 1.3 percent, to
5,178.52. The  FTSE All-Share Index  declined 1.2 percent and
Ireland’s  ISEQ Index  fell 2.4 percent.  
 Barclays Plc  (BARC LN): The bank increased the size of two
offerings of 15-year callable step-up notes to a total of $145
million, according to prospectuses filed with the U.S.
Securities and Exchange Commission. The shares fell 3.2 percent
to 300.8 pence.  
 DSG International Plc  (DSGI LN): The U.K. consumer
electronics retailer that owns Currys and PC World is scheduled
to report earnings. The stock advanced 0.3 percent to 27.5
pence.  
 DS Smith Plc  (SMDS LN): The owner of the Spicers office
products brand is due to report earnings. The shares declined
2.9 percent to 120 pence.  
 Go-Ahead Group Plc  (GOG LN): London’s biggest bus operator
is due to release a trading update. The stock fell 1.9 percent
to 1,319 pence.  
 Micro Focus International Plc  (MCRO LN): The business
software maker is scheduled to report earnings. The stock fell
2.6 percent to 527.5 pence.  
 Petrofac Ltd.  (PFC LN): The U.K. oil-services provider is
due to release a trading statement. The shares declined 0.4
percent to 1,251 pence.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Ben Martin  in London   bmartin38@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        